ial scales, with characteristic delays of $\\tau_1=4.1\\pm 0.3\\ \\mu{\\rm\ns}$ and $\\tau_2=23\\pm 3\\ \\mu{\\rm s}$, indicating the presence of two scales of\nscattering in the interstellar medium. These two scales are present in the\npulse-broadening function. The longer scale contains 0.38 times the scattered\npower of the shorter one. We suggest that the longer tail arises from\nhighly-scattered paths, possibly from anisotropic scattering or from\nsubstructure at large angles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Jan 2015 10:52:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 19 Oct 2015 16:01:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 15 Mar 2016 19:22:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-13"}
